# Segments — tiers & scoring rubric   (OPTIONAL)
#
# Copy to context/segments.md if you want the qualifier to tier and score contacts.
# If absent, the qualifier still runs but treats all in-ICP contacts as one tier.
# The qualifier keeps the MECHANISM (classify company → score contact → present for
# human review); it reads the CRITERIA from this file.

## Segment A (primary — pursue aggressively)
<Criteria that put an account in your best tier. e.g. "200–2,000 employees,
B2B SaaS, has RevOps, in a default-geography country">

## Segment B (adjacent — pursue selectively)
<Criteria for a worth-it-but-not-ideal account.>

## Segment C (exclude / deprioritize)
<Criteria that knock an account out. Hard exclusions also belong in exclusions.md.>

## Scoring rubric (0–10)
- Persona match: 0–4   (exact title+seniority = 4; adjacent = 2; weak = 0)
- Company fit:   0–3   (Segment A = 3; B = 1–2; C = 0)
- Data completeness: 0–2   (has linkedin_url + company_domain = 2)
- Novelty:       0–1   (not already in your CRM / not previously contacted = 1)

## Thresholds
- QUALIFY  >= 7
- MAYBE    4–6   (surface for human review)
- SKIP     <= 3
